<p><b>Message</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Transmutation" title="Transmutation" class="mw-redirect">transmutation</a> <a href="/wiki/Cantrip" title="Cantrip" class="mw-redirect">cantrip</a> available to <a href="/wiki/Bard" title="Bard">bards</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sorcerer" title="Sorcerer">sorcerers</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Wizard" title="Wizard">wizards</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-spellLists_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellLists-1">[2]</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Description"> Description </span></h2>
<p>You point at a <a href="/wiki/Creature" title="Creature">creature</a> and whisper a message that only it can hear, and it can whisper back a reply that only you hear. You can cast through objects if you know the target and that it's beyond the wall, but <a href="/wiki/Silence" title="Silence">magical silence</a>, 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of metals, a thin sheet of lead, and 3 feet of wood will block the spell. The spell can move through corners and other openings.<sup id="cite_ref-spellDesc_0-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellDesc-0">[1]</a></sup>
</p>
